
00:00:15,407 --> 00:00:17,343
Urine.

00:00:17,409 --> 00:00:18,644
(sniffing)

00:00:18,711 --> 00:00:19,912
I don't smell it.

00:00:19,979 --> 00:00:20,980
Ever since
Father started

00:00:21,046 --> 00:00:22,548
leaving the church
open at night.

00:00:22,615 --> 00:00:24,483
The church has gotten
a lot more use.

00:00:24,550 --> 00:00:26,519
Yeah, as an orgy house
and a toilet.

00:00:26,585 --> 00:00:29,788
No. People come in at all hours
of the night to pray.

00:00:29,855 --> 00:00:32,925
"Dear Jesus, please keep me from
blowing all my laundry money

00:00:32,992 --> 00:00:35,661
on the nickel slots
at the Gas 'N' Go."

00:00:40,266 --> 00:00:42,134
Oh, somebody's done
their business

00:00:42,201 --> 00:00:43,702
right here
next to Jesus.

00:00:43,769 --> 00:00:45,771
Oh, no, not again.

00:00:58,284 --> 00:01:02,254
Right here on the eve
of the apocalypse, a miracle.

00:01:15,734 --> 00:01:17,736
(garbled radio transmissions)

00:01:22,141 --> 00:01:24,677
Somebody went to a lot of
trouble to get her up there.

00:01:24,743 --> 00:01:26,712
Why? I wonder.

00:01:26,779 --> 00:01:29,415
Somebody had a grudge
against the church

00:01:29,481 --> 00:01:30,649
or somebody
in the church.

00:01:30,716 --> 00:01:34,053
Or maybe they were
just mad at God.

00:01:37,790 --> 00:01:39,525
Well, Jesus died
for our sins.

00:01:39,592 --> 00:01:42,695
What sin did she die for?

00:01:49,602 --> 00:01:52,705
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:01:52,771 --> 00:01:55,274
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:01:55,341 --> 00:01:58,644
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:01:58,711 --> 00:02:00,412
♪ Who, who, who, who? ♪

00:02:00,479 --> 00:02:02,381
♪ I really wanna know ♪

00:02:02,448 --> 00:02:04,984
♪ Who... are you? ♪

00:02:05,050 --> 00:02:06,886
♪ Oh-oh-oh ♪
♪ <i>Who... ♪</i>

00:02:06,952 --> 00:02:10,089
♪ Come on, tell me
who are you, you, you ♪

00:02:10,155 --> 00:02:12,258
♪ Are you! ♪

00:02:14,609 --> 00:02:16,077
(camera clicking)

00:02:26,154 --> 00:02:28,623
You know, if you
think about it,

00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:32,460
this is one of the oldest ways
to kill somebody.

00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:35,930
Considering where we are,
highly symbolic.

00:02:35,997 --> 00:02:37,165
All right, what do you got?

00:02:37,232 --> 00:02:38,466
How we gonna do this?

00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:39,634
Well, the two-by-four is tied

00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:42,470
to the scaffold
with a single loop.

00:02:42,537 --> 00:02:45,974
There is an empty pulley
up here.

00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,575
We could lower her down
with that.

00:02:47,642 --> 00:02:48,910
That's probably how the killer

00:02:48,977 --> 00:02:50,845
got her up there
in the first place.

00:02:50,912 --> 00:02:52,747
Then he ditched the rope.

00:02:52,814 --> 00:02:55,216
I wouldn't be surprised to find
it around here someplace.

00:02:55,283 --> 00:02:56,651
First things first.

00:02:56,718 --> 00:03:00,255
We'll use our rope;
I'll run it through this pulley,

00:03:00,322 --> 00:03:02,490
and then let you
take the weight.

00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:05,493
I'll mark the rope,
cut the knot;

00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:08,129
down she goes.

00:03:16,304 --> 00:03:17,706
Ready?

00:03:17,772 --> 00:03:18,940
Yeah.

00:03:19,007 --> 00:03:20,508
You take the weight.
I'll cut it on three.

00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:21,509
One,

00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:23,345
two,

00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:24,679
three.

00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,348
Got it?

00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:27,615
Yeah, ready.

00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:30,285
Oh.

00:03:30,352 --> 00:03:31,419
Whoever tied her up there

00:03:31,486 --> 00:03:33,488
had to be strong enough
to deadlift her weight.

00:03:33,555 --> 00:03:34,622
Yeah, either that
or highly motivated.

00:03:34,689 --> 00:03:36,925
You know how it is

00:03:36,992 --> 00:03:38,927
once somebody's
adrenaline gets pumping.

00:03:38,994 --> 00:03:40,829
Feel like they
can do anything.

00:03:47,869 --> 00:03:50,005
All right, that's it.

00:04:00,548 --> 00:04:01,750
(siren whoops)

00:04:01,816 --> 00:04:05,020
(garbled radio transmission)

00:04:06,287 --> 00:04:08,356
Look, shouldn't Father
Frank be here by now?

00:04:08,423 --> 00:04:10,692
Father Frank lives
in manana land.

00:04:10,759 --> 00:04:12,694
Well, I'm sure
he's on his way.

00:04:12,761 --> 00:04:14,663
Father Frank is
a wonderful priest.

00:04:14,729 --> 00:04:17,232
And since he's been here,
church attendance has tripled.

00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:19,300
Among our female congregants.

00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:21,202
(sighs)
And we have

00:04:21,269 --> 00:04:23,004
sponsors for
our building fund.

00:04:23,071 --> 00:04:24,305
One sponsor.

00:04:24,372 --> 00:04:25,273
The Big Hombre?

00:04:26,408 --> 00:04:28,176
The car dealership.

00:04:28,243 --> 00:04:30,478
Time of death
was sometime

00:04:30,545 --> 00:04:33,148
between 2:00
and 4:00.

00:04:33,214 --> 00:04:34,649
Nasty head wound.

00:04:34,716 --> 00:04:38,053
She was actively bleeding,
so she had to have been alive

00:04:38,119 --> 00:04:40,655
when she was tied
to the cross.

00:04:40,722 --> 00:04:42,891
Good chance she died
of suffocation.

00:04:42,957 --> 00:04:44,592
Like Jesus.

00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:46,561
Well, Jesus had
a footrest.

00:04:46,628 --> 00:04:49,764
He was able to lift himself up
and take short breaths.

00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:51,433
But this young lady was hanging.

00:04:51,499 --> 00:04:53,735
Her pectoral muscles

00:04:53,802 --> 00:04:55,303
probably became
paralyzed

00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:57,672
and the intercostal muscles
were unable to function.

00:04:57,739 --> 00:05:00,508
She was able to breathe out,
but not breathe in.

00:05:00,575 --> 00:05:03,144
<i>In time, carbon dioxide</i>
<i>built up</i>

00:05:03,211 --> 00:05:04,479
<i>in her lungs and bloodstream.</i>

00:05:04,546 --> 00:05:06,181
<i>Edema built up</i>
<i>in the chest cavity.</i>

00:05:06,247 --> 00:05:07,849
<i>Heart went into fibrillation.</i>

00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:09,050
(heart beating rapidly)

00:05:09,117 --> 00:05:12,954
Gruesome torture in any century.

00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:14,789
WILLOWS:
In 18 years, this is
my first crucifixion.

00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:19,060
In a Catholic church
with no crucifixes.

00:05:19,127 --> 00:05:20,195
GRISSOM:
I imagine the priest

00:05:20,261 --> 00:05:22,230
is a resurrection
theologian,

00:05:22,297 --> 00:05:24,933
as opposed to
a crucifixion theologian.

00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,534
They believe in forgiveness

00:05:26,601 --> 00:05:27,769
rather than penance.

00:05:27,836 --> 00:05:29,571
We could all use
a little forgiveness.

00:05:29,637 --> 00:05:31,039
She was bleeding
from her head wounds,

00:05:31,106 --> 00:05:33,141
and the beating didn't
take place up there.

00:05:34,809 --> 00:05:36,511
WILLOWS:
Well, the blood pool
is gravitational.

00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:39,848
And the blood trail...

00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:45,787
...the tips are pointing
towards the statue.

00:05:45,854 --> 00:05:48,256
She was bleeding on the way in.

00:05:48,323 --> 00:05:52,160
I'll backtrack, see if I can
find the point of origin.

00:05:52,227 --> 00:05:54,229
Excuse me, huh?

00:05:56,865 --> 00:05:58,600
I-I got to go, Father.
I'll see you.

00:05:58,667 --> 00:05:59,634
Okay.

00:05:59,701 --> 00:06:01,403
I'm the pastor of the church.

00:06:01,469 --> 00:06:02,570
Hey, Captain.

00:06:02,637 --> 00:06:03,605
He'll take
care of you.

00:06:03,672 --> 00:06:05,607
Thank you.

00:06:05,674 --> 00:06:07,676
Father Frank Berlin.

00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:09,077
I'm Jim Brass, Las Vegas Police.

00:06:09,144 --> 00:06:11,179
You were supposed to be here
45 minutes ago. Where you been?

00:06:11,246 --> 00:06:13,248
Been serving breakfast
at the shelter.

00:06:13,315 --> 00:06:14,916
I understand there's been
a death in the church.

00:06:14,983 --> 00:06:16,184
How soon before
you're out of here?

00:06:16,251 --> 00:06:18,953
Father, this is
a murder investigation.

00:06:19,020 --> 00:06:20,355
It's just
we hold Mass at 10:00.

00:06:20,422 --> 00:06:21,623
Yeah, I understand.

00:06:21,690 --> 00:06:24,426
Sorry, Father, but, uh,
this is a crime scene.

00:06:24,492 --> 00:06:26,227
You're not gonna get
your church back for a while.

00:06:26,294 --> 00:06:28,430
Is it all right if we set Mass
in the community center?

00:06:28,496 --> 00:06:30,332
Yeah, sure, I have
no problem with that.

00:06:30,398 --> 00:06:32,467
FRANK:
Sister, would you
tell the choir

00:06:32,534 --> 00:06:33,835
we'll be singing
"In Paradisum."

00:06:33,902 --> 00:06:35,570
I'll take care
of it, Father.

00:06:35,637 --> 00:06:38,073
We sing the hymn for the dead
every time we have a death.

00:06:38,139 --> 00:06:40,075
Sisters couldn't
identify the victim,

00:06:40,141 --> 00:06:42,043
so we'll need you
to take a look.

00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:43,878
Sorry. I didn't mean
to sound cavalier.

00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:46,348
It's just we've had over
half a dozen deaths this year.

00:06:46,414 --> 00:06:48,216
We've never had to close
the church.

00:06:48,283 --> 00:06:49,651
That's because,
in this neighborhood,

00:06:49,718 --> 00:06:52,287
those derelicts and drug addicts
died of heatstroke, overdose

00:06:52,354 --> 00:06:54,089
and old age.

00:06:54,155 --> 00:06:56,057
None of them were strung
up in the rafters.

00:06:56,124 --> 00:06:58,693
Father Frank Berlin,
this is Gil Grissom

00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,362
from the crime lab.

00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:06,735
Do you recognize her?

00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:14,676
I'll take that
as a no.

00:07:15,610 --> 00:07:17,078
Excuse me, Father.

00:07:17,145 --> 00:07:18,780
Is that blood
on your jacket?

00:07:20,582 --> 00:07:22,651
We had a fight in the shelter.

00:07:22,717 --> 00:07:23,918
I had to break it up.

00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,520
We're gonna need
to take your clothes.

00:07:25,587 --> 00:07:27,322
No, you can't have my clothes.

00:07:27,389 --> 00:07:28,556
BRASS:
Then you have to come

00:07:28,623 --> 00:07:30,025
downtown to the police station.

00:07:30,091 --> 00:07:31,259
If you're gonna
say Mass later,

00:07:31,326 --> 00:07:35,030
you have to change
anyway, right?

00:07:35,096 --> 00:07:37,966
Greg, go with him,
collect his clothing.

00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:44,372
Is it a bigger sin to lie
if you're a priest?

00:07:44,439 --> 00:07:46,775
I hope so.

00:08:18,606 --> 00:08:21,142
(strikes match)

00:08:21,209 --> 00:08:24,012
This one's for you, Sam.

00:08:35,657 --> 00:08:37,192
When will I get those back?

00:08:37,258 --> 00:08:39,094
I only have
three sets of clothes.

00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:41,796
Respectfully, Father, a woman's
been murdered in your church

00:08:41,863 --> 00:08:43,264
and your clothes
have blood on them.

00:08:43,331 --> 00:08:45,266
You're lucky you're
not under arrest.

00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:47,335
(choir singing ethereal song
in foreign language)

00:09:17,298 --> 00:09:19,300
♪ ♪

00:09:47,395 --> 00:09:49,397
♪ ♪

00:10:07,382 --> 00:10:10,385
♪ ♪

00:10:14,456 --> 00:10:17,392
Was there bougainvillea
at the crime scene?

00:10:19,427 --> 00:10:21,663
Two shrubs at the
entrance of the church.

00:10:23,431 --> 00:10:26,534
A row of four on the wall
of the community center.

00:10:26,601 --> 00:10:29,571
Three bushes behind the rectory

00:10:29,637 --> 00:10:31,573
adjacent to the statue
of St. Jude.

00:10:31,639 --> 00:10:33,842
Did you anticipate that question

00:10:33,908 --> 00:10:36,211
in order to impress me with
your powers of observation?

00:10:36,277 --> 00:10:37,579
Memory's a gift.

00:10:37,646 --> 00:10:38,647
Mmm.

00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:41,416
From whom?

00:10:41,483 --> 00:10:44,119
Who do you think?

00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:47,689
Well, I wouldn't necessarily
call myself an atheist,

00:10:47,756 --> 00:10:50,759
but I am not sold on the notion
of a higher power.

00:10:50,825 --> 00:10:52,594
However,

00:10:52,661 --> 00:10:54,429
I used to love
the stories

00:10:54,496 --> 00:10:55,964
of the saint.

00:10:56,031 --> 00:10:58,633
This job certainly
challenges your faith.

00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:00,135
Yes, it does.

00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:01,936
But I have science.

00:11:02,003 --> 00:11:05,573
I believe we need
a little of both.

00:11:07,609 --> 00:11:09,311
Sometimes

00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:11,946
I think
we made up God

00:11:12,013 --> 00:11:14,949
just to have someone
to blame for our mistakes.

00:11:19,621 --> 00:11:22,123
It's just a theory.

00:11:23,992 --> 00:11:27,996
♪ ♪

00:11:56,057 --> 00:12:00,428
♪ ♪

00:12:09,337 --> 00:12:12,107
(car alarm blares)

00:12:26,921 --> 00:12:30,925
♪ ♪

00:12:56,951 --> 00:13:03,024
♪ ♪

00:13:28,416 --> 00:13:30,752
(chuckling):
Hey.

00:13:30,819 --> 00:13:32,020
Hey!

00:13:32,087 --> 00:13:34,022
Hey, I found it.

00:13:34,089 --> 00:13:38,660
Rope, nails, hammers,
everything.

00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,435
Oh, yeah.

00:14:05,754 --> 00:14:07,756
Something I said?

00:14:07,822 --> 00:14:09,691
No, dear.

00:14:10,825 --> 00:14:12,894
I didn't offend you,
did I?

00:14:12,961 --> 00:14:15,764
Did I say something offensive
to you as a Catholic?

00:14:15,830 --> 00:14:18,533
I'm not really a Catholic
anymore, you know.

00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:21,970
I suppose I practice a kind
of secular Catholicism

00:14:22,037 --> 00:14:25,006
that involves ritualizing
certain aspects of everyday life

00:14:25,073 --> 00:14:26,741
and imbuing them with

00:14:26,808 --> 00:14:30,378
a spiritual intensity
they might not
otherwise possess,

00:14:30,445 --> 00:14:32,914
but I don't want to put
too fine a point on it.

00:14:35,216 --> 00:14:38,720
And the rosary beads
are a part of that.

00:14:38,787 --> 00:14:40,855
This belonged to my mother.

00:14:43,525 --> 00:14:45,727
Take a look
at this pattern.

00:15:01,977 --> 00:15:03,945
Five series of
ten beads each

00:15:04,012 --> 00:15:05,246
representing the
"Five Mysteries"

00:15:05,313 --> 00:15:07,882
separated by five
"Our Father" beads.

00:15:07,949 --> 00:15:10,952
Who would strangle someone
with a rosary?

00:15:11,019 --> 00:15:12,253
Probably the same person

00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:14,589
who would crucify someone
in a church.

00:15:33,671 --> 00:15:35,773
St. Jude.

00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:37,742
Patron saint of lost causes.

00:15:37,808 --> 00:15:39,477
And that's why it's
so difficult to keep

00:15:39,544 --> 00:15:41,245
the local kids from
defacing this statue.

00:15:41,312 --> 00:15:44,081
Did you run those tests
on my clothes?

00:15:44,148 --> 00:15:46,584
We did. The blood
on your clothes is not a match

00:15:46,651 --> 00:15:47,818
to the blood on the victim.

00:15:47,885 --> 00:15:49,487
So do I get my clothes back?

00:15:49,554 --> 00:15:50,688
Not just yet.

00:15:51,722 --> 00:15:53,024
I have a favor to ask.

00:15:53,090 --> 00:15:54,225
You steal my clothes

00:15:54,292 --> 00:15:56,093
and then you want to ask
for another favor?

00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:58,496
We'd like permission
to search your rectory

00:15:58,563 --> 00:15:59,897
and the nun's apartments.

00:15:59,964 --> 00:16:01,966
Just because
someone dies in our church

00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:03,834
doesn't mean we have anything
to do with it.

00:16:03,901 --> 00:16:06,170
Well, we want to eliminate you
as suspects.

00:16:06,237 --> 00:16:08,773
That's what you said
when you fingerprinted us,

00:16:08,839 --> 00:16:10,908
and the truth is you don't
have enough for a warrant.

00:16:10,975 --> 00:16:12,043
You're right.

00:16:12,109 --> 00:16:13,511
But you have nothing to hide.

00:16:15,546 --> 00:16:17,114
You really think
if I killed a woman,

00:16:17,181 --> 00:16:19,684
I'd leave her body
in my own church?
It's so obvious

00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,986
that it obviates suspicion.

00:16:22,053 --> 00:16:24,121
Mmm, I'm not that smart.

00:16:24,188 --> 00:16:25,856
Well, that's hardly
the argument to make.

00:16:25,923 --> 00:16:27,525
What is it you're looking for?

00:16:27,592 --> 00:16:28,793
Rosaries.

00:16:28,859 --> 00:16:32,430
Mr. Grissom,
I didn't realize you were here.

00:16:32,496 --> 00:16:33,464
That's all right, Sister.

00:16:33,531 --> 00:16:35,633
We don't have to hide anything
from Mr. Grissom.

00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:38,069
Uh, he's here
to confiscate our rosaries.

00:16:38,135 --> 00:16:39,704
I don't know where mine are.
Do you?

00:16:39,770 --> 00:16:42,006
It's probably in the sacristy.

00:16:42,073 --> 00:16:43,774
We'll need all the rosaries.

00:16:43,841 --> 00:16:46,210
Uh, even Sister Elizabeth's?

00:16:46,277 --> 00:16:49,013
She's not going to like that.

00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:50,481
Happy day for Sister Elizabeth,

00:16:50,548 --> 00:16:52,216
for she delights

00:16:52,283 --> 00:16:54,819
in what she dislikes.

00:16:57,355 --> 00:17:01,359
♪ ♪

00:17:16,207 --> 00:17:19,877
The killer used materials
from the church:

00:17:19,944 --> 00:17:23,080
the rope, the 2x4s,
and one of these hammers.

00:17:23,147 --> 00:17:25,316
I just haven't
found it yet.

00:17:25,383 --> 00:17:27,885
But all this was
in the same utility closet.

00:17:27,952 --> 00:17:29,654
He didn't bring
anything with him?
Hmm-mm.

00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:31,589
What does this
feel like to you?

00:17:31,656 --> 00:17:33,691
Inside job.

00:17:33,758 --> 00:17:35,560
I mean maybe one
of the construction workers

00:17:35,626 --> 00:17:38,062
wasn't a fan
of the victim.

00:17:38,129 --> 00:17:39,597
I'm going to call Brass.

00:17:46,137 --> 00:17:47,104
What?

00:17:47,171 --> 00:17:48,206
I've solved your case.

00:17:48,272 --> 00:17:49,941
Bull.
No, cow.

00:17:50,007 --> 00:17:51,976
Those hairs you found
on the scaffold:

00:17:52,043 --> 00:17:53,077
not human.

00:17:53,144 --> 00:17:54,345
Bovine.

00:17:56,447 --> 00:17:57,848
They have red cows?

00:17:57,915 --> 00:18:00,017
You betcha, partner.
Guernseys.

00:18:00,084 --> 00:18:02,553
Maybe the scaffold
was used somewhere else.

00:18:02,620 --> 00:18:03,588
Like on a farm.

00:18:03,654 --> 00:18:05,756
Or maybe it was
secondary transfer.

00:18:05,823 --> 00:18:07,225
Well, you can
take care of that.

00:18:07,291 --> 00:18:08,960
I've done all
the heavy lifting.

00:18:09,026 --> 00:18:10,294
As usual.

00:18:15,933 --> 00:18:17,869
Oh, hi.
Hi.

00:18:17,935 --> 00:18:19,303
I saw you
at the crime scene.

00:18:19,370 --> 00:18:21,572
I thought you were on desk duty
until the coroner's inquest.

00:18:21,639 --> 00:18:23,407
Yeah, I was starting
to get a serious case

00:18:23,474 --> 00:18:26,010
of trucker butt so I told
Grissom that I wanted to, uh,

00:18:26,077 --> 00:18:27,879
get back out with the team.

00:18:27,945 --> 00:18:30,982
Yeah, there's no
therapy like work.

00:18:31,048 --> 00:18:33,284
You doing okay?

00:18:33,351 --> 00:18:35,486
Yeah.

00:18:35,553 --> 00:18:37,722
Well, hang in there.

00:18:37,788 --> 00:18:39,557
All right.

00:18:43,594 --> 00:18:45,463
(sighs)

00:18:48,633 --> 00:18:50,034
Mr. Bombay.

00:18:50,101 --> 00:18:52,670
We found your keys
at the scene of our murder.

00:18:52,737 --> 00:18:55,106
We also found
your car close by.

00:18:57,608 --> 00:18:59,277
I don't know anything
about a murder.

00:18:59,343 --> 00:19:01,712
Well, we also found
a wad of bloody tissues

00:19:01,779 --> 00:19:03,447
