00:19:03,514 --> 00:19:04,916
What... what's going on?

00:19:04,982 --> 00:19:06,417
You tell me.

00:19:06,484 --> 00:19:09,153
I loaned my car to a woman
I work with last night.

00:19:09,220 --> 00:19:10,521
She sings at my club.

00:19:10,588 --> 00:19:12,823
Charlotte Danville.
Is she all right?

00:19:12,890 --> 00:19:15,192
Was this your friend?

00:19:20,264 --> 00:19:21,999
Yeah, that's her.

00:19:23,034 --> 00:19:24,936
Who did... who did this to her?

00:19:25,002 --> 00:19:26,470
Why did she borrow your car?

00:19:26,537 --> 00:19:28,472
She had to...
She had to do another set

00:19:28,539 --> 00:19:29,707
and needed
to change her clothes.

00:19:29,774 --> 00:19:31,142
Doesn't she have her own car?

00:19:31,209 --> 00:19:32,543
She had a Lexus.

00:19:32,610 --> 00:19:34,045
Totally tricked out.

00:19:34,111 --> 00:19:35,213
So why did she borrow yours?

00:19:35,279 --> 00:19:36,314
I don't know.

00:19:36,380 --> 00:19:37,715
I didn't get the whole story.

00:19:37,782 --> 00:19:39,050
She seemed upset.

00:19:39,116 --> 00:19:41,185
She was talking to this guy.

00:19:41,252 --> 00:19:44,355
<i>I had to send a waitress over</i>
<i>to remind her</i>

00:19:44,422 --> 00:19:46,290
<i>that she was</i>
<i>getting paid to sing.</i>

00:19:46,357 --> 00:19:48,125
You ever see the
guy move forward?

00:19:48,192 --> 00:19:50,828
<i>Yeah, it's that guy</i>
<i>that sells cars on television.</i>

00:19:50,895 --> 00:19:53,497
Uh... Cody White.

00:19:53,564 --> 00:19:54,865
The Big Hombre.

00:19:54,932 --> 00:19:57,335
I mean, but a lot of guys
came in to see Charlotte.

00:19:57,401 --> 00:19:59,170
I mean, it's not like
she slept around or anything.

00:19:59,237 --> 00:20:01,138
I tried.

00:20:01,205 --> 00:20:02,907
Can I go now?

00:20:02,974 --> 00:20:05,243
Not without an alibi.

00:20:05,309 --> 00:20:06,611
Where did you
spend the night?

00:20:06,677 --> 00:20:08,980
I allowed myself to succumb
to the pleasures of Donna.

00:20:09,046 --> 00:20:11,449
And she kept me up
to the wee hours of the morning

00:20:11,515 --> 00:20:13,618
gratifying her abnormal lust.

00:20:18,022 --> 00:20:20,057
She sleeps with her eyes open.

00:20:26,430 --> 00:20:28,432
Yeah, this is it.

00:20:28,499 --> 00:20:30,935
Well, this car's already
been cleaned and detailed.

00:20:31,002 --> 00:20:32,236
It's ready to be sold.

00:20:32,303 --> 00:20:34,405
Well, I guess it's
a change of plans.
No.

00:20:34,472 --> 00:20:36,173
No, there's not
a change of planes.

00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:38,009
This baby's staying
right where she sits.

00:20:38,075 --> 00:20:39,777
I'm not in the
give-away-the-car-to-cops
business.

00:20:39,844 --> 00:20:41,913
I'm in the sell-the-car-
to-willing-victims business.

00:20:41,979 --> 00:20:43,848
Mr. White, we have
a court order

00:20:43,915 --> 00:20:45,750
to examine this car
for evidence related

00:20:45,816 --> 00:20:47,351
to the murder of
Charlotte Danville.

00:20:47,418 --> 00:20:48,920
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
Charlotte?

00:20:48,986 --> 00:20:50,888
She and I are friends.

00:20:50,955 --> 00:20:51,956
I... I knew her.

00:20:52,023 --> 00:20:53,591
Yeah, I know.
We have a witness

00:20:53,658 --> 00:20:55,526
who places you arguing
with her last night.

00:20:55,593 --> 00:20:57,895
You may be one of the last
people to see her alive.

00:20:57,962 --> 00:20:59,096
Yeah.

00:20:59,163 --> 00:21:00,431
I was with her.

00:21:00,498 --> 00:21:02,967
I went to see Charlotte
to give her the car.

00:21:03,034 --> 00:21:04,569
Helped Charlotte
through

00:21:04,635 --> 00:21:06,304
a rough patch,
but lately she been ducking me.

00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:07,905
What am I supposed to do now?

00:21:07,972 --> 00:21:09,640
Walk home?

00:21:09,707 --> 00:21:11,275
I'll give you
money for a cab.

00:21:11,342 --> 00:21:13,411
Tomorrow, we'll see about
getting you a good used car.

00:21:13,477 --> 00:21:15,079
Some junker.

00:21:15,146 --> 00:21:16,914
Thanks a lot.

00:21:16,981 --> 00:21:18,416
Some friend you are.

00:21:18,482 --> 00:21:19,684
Take your damn car.

00:21:21,886 --> 00:21:25,823
Guess that's what you get
for helping a friend, you know.

00:21:25,890 --> 00:21:29,093
Look, I feel awful about
about Charlotte. I really do.

00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,328
But I'll tell you this:

00:21:30,394 --> 00:21:32,263
whatever happened
happened after I got this car.

00:21:32,330 --> 00:21:34,999
Well, I feel awful too, but
the car is coming with me.

00:21:35,066 --> 00:21:38,102
WILLOWS:
<i>No sign of forced entry.</i>

00:21:40,338 --> 00:21:42,840
Does this look
like the condo

00:21:42,907 --> 00:21:44,876
of a woman who
sings weekends

00:21:44,942 --> 00:21:46,510
at the Gorilla Room?

00:21:46,577 --> 00:21:49,413
Looks like the fight
started here.

00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:53,484
Got some blood, some
here on the pillow.

00:21:53,551 --> 00:21:55,820
But no blood trail.

00:21:55,887 --> 00:21:58,589
The real beating took place
in the bushes at the church.

00:21:58,656 --> 00:22:00,458
This was just the opening act.

00:22:00,524 --> 00:22:03,661
Explains the bloody tissue found
in the backseat of Hugo's car.

00:22:03,728 --> 00:22:07,798
I guess she got a bloody
nose or a fat lip here,

00:22:07,865 --> 00:22:11,335
ran out and used Hugo's car
to go to the church.

00:22:11,402 --> 00:22:14,405
CURTIS:
The killer must have
followed her

00:22:14,472 --> 00:22:16,140
and caught up
with her there.

00:22:19,277 --> 00:22:21,412
She had quite the career.

00:22:27,184 --> 00:22:28,185
Sofia.

00:22:30,187 --> 00:22:31,188
You recognize that guy?

00:22:31,255 --> 00:22:34,392
Father Frank.

00:22:34,458 --> 00:22:37,628
I mean, a lot
younger, obviously.

00:22:37,695 --> 00:22:40,731
You know him?

00:22:40,798 --> 00:22:41,933
No.

00:22:41,999 --> 00:22:43,000
That's the Big Hombre.

00:22:43,067 --> 00:22:45,603
He sells cars on TV.

00:22:45,670 --> 00:22:47,905
She's known these guys forever.

00:22:57,548 --> 00:22:58,916
Here's a rosary.

00:23:00,284 --> 00:23:02,186
Looks like
it's broken.

00:23:06,090 --> 00:23:09,393
Hmm. Could be the one
she was strangled with.

00:23:11,462 --> 00:23:13,764
And here's her purse

00:23:13,831 --> 00:23:16,334
and cell phone.

00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:18,102
You don't leave home without
those unless you're in a hurry.

00:23:18,169 --> 00:23:21,706
Or you're
being chased.

00:23:21,772 --> 00:23:24,275
TV's on pause.

00:23:24,342 --> 00:23:27,345
(singing karaoke on TV)

00:23:27,411 --> 00:23:30,248
Well, there they are again.

00:23:30,314 --> 00:23:31,749
Someone was taking a trip

00:23:31,816 --> 00:23:33,951
down memory lane.

00:23:34,018 --> 00:23:36,087
♪ They tear us apart ♪

00:23:39,423 --> 00:23:41,425
There was a man in her life.

00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,636
Mr. Frisky.

00:23:51,702 --> 00:23:55,706
Drain smells like whiskey,
empty bottles in the trash,

00:23:55,773 --> 00:23:58,576
more liquor than you could
use in a wild weekend.

00:23:58,643 --> 00:24:01,012
She might have been
going on the wagon.

00:24:04,015 --> 00:24:07,218
Folic acid.

00:24:07,285 --> 00:24:10,288
Fresh fruit, vegetables,
plenty of milk.

00:24:14,525 --> 00:24:17,061
You think
she was pregnant?

00:24:17,128 --> 00:24:19,497
We'll have Robbins
run a pregnancy test.

00:24:26,704 --> 00:24:28,039
(computer beeps)

00:24:33,177 --> 00:24:35,146
(beeping continues)

00:24:51,862 --> 00:24:53,864
♪ ♪

00:25:07,812 --> 00:25:09,080
Hey.

00:25:09,146 --> 00:25:10,982
Got another rosary
for your collection.

00:25:11,048 --> 00:25:14,051
Where'd you get this?

00:25:14,118 --> 00:25:15,686
Catherine found it
in Charlotte's condo.

00:25:15,753 --> 00:25:16,954
There is some evidence

00:25:17,021 --> 00:25:18,189
that the fight
started there.

00:25:18,256 --> 00:25:20,758
Charlotte's bag and
cell phone were there,

00:25:20,825 --> 00:25:24,662
as if she left
in a hurry.

00:25:24,729 --> 00:25:27,965
Are those
Father Frank's?

00:25:28,032 --> 00:25:29,200
Yeah.

00:25:33,070 --> 00:25:34,205
Where's Father Frank?

00:25:34,272 --> 00:25:37,842
Father Frank is hearing
confessions tonight.

00:25:37,909 --> 00:25:40,044
It's St. Bart's
all over again.

00:25:40,111 --> 00:25:42,280
Only that time, he
went in handcuffs.

00:25:42,346 --> 00:25:43,581
That never happened.

00:25:43,648 --> 00:25:45,182
It was just a rumor.

00:25:49,287 --> 00:25:50,288
(grunts loudly)

00:25:51,389 --> 00:25:52,723
Hey!

00:25:54,792 --> 00:25:56,594
Didn't your mother tell you

00:25:56,661 --> 00:25:58,195
you're not supposed
to fight in church?

00:25:58,262 --> 00:25:59,897
Cody White.

00:25:59,964 --> 00:26:00,898
What's up, hombre?

00:26:00,965 --> 00:26:03,301
Father Frank and I
are actually old friends.

00:26:05,403 --> 00:26:07,271
Just having a conversation
about church finances.

00:26:07,338 --> 00:26:08,306
But aren't you the one

00:26:08,372 --> 00:26:09,740
who's funding the renovation
of the church?

00:26:09,807 --> 00:26:10,908
Not anymore.

00:26:10,975 --> 00:26:14,178
Well, there you go.

00:26:14,245 --> 00:26:15,279
We done here?

00:26:15,346 --> 00:26:17,215
BRASS:
Yeah.

00:26:19,317 --> 00:26:21,953
So what sins did he commit

00:26:22,019 --> 00:26:23,454
to earn
the punch-out penance?

00:26:23,521 --> 00:26:25,790
Let's talk
about it downtown.

00:26:39,663 --> 00:26:42,266
GRISSOM:
These are unique rosaries,
Father.

00:26:42,333 --> 00:26:44,735
Handmade in Italy.

00:26:44,802 --> 00:26:46,337
And they're
sequentially numbered

00:26:46,403 --> 00:26:47,872
on the back.

00:26:49,006 --> 00:26:51,609
So we know that they were
purchased together.

00:26:51,675 --> 00:26:54,912
One of them is yours; one we
found at the victim's condo.

00:26:54,979 --> 00:26:56,780
Did you give it to her?

00:26:56,847 --> 00:26:58,148
Yes.

00:26:58,215 --> 00:27:00,384
BRASS:
You know, Father, when we
asked you if you knew her,

00:27:00,451 --> 00:27:03,087
you said you didn't.

00:27:03,153 --> 00:27:06,156
After I saw Charlotte's body,

00:27:06,223 --> 00:27:09,126
I don't recall
being asked any questions.

00:27:09,193 --> 00:27:13,464
Um, uh, maybe I said "no"
to what I was seeing.

00:27:13,531 --> 00:27:15,599
I don't really remember
much about yesterday.

00:27:15,666 --> 00:27:17,868
What about the night before?

00:27:17,935 --> 00:27:19,770
I was at the shelter.

00:27:19,837 --> 00:27:21,972
You know,
we can't find anyone

00:27:22,039 --> 00:27:23,707
who remembers seeing you there
after midnight.

00:27:23,774 --> 00:27:26,076
Because I wasn't there
past midnight.

00:27:26,143 --> 00:27:26,977
Where were you?

00:27:27,044 --> 00:27:28,612
One of our regulars, Marty,

00:27:28,679 --> 00:27:30,014
came in high on crack.

00:27:30,080 --> 00:27:31,315
He got into an argument,

00:27:31,382 --> 00:27:33,784
a fight with one
of the other men, and I...

00:27:33,851 --> 00:27:34,652
What time was that?

00:27:34,718 --> 00:27:36,420
Uh, it was late.

00:27:36,487 --> 00:27:37,888
I don't wear a watch.
We had to call

00:27:37,955 --> 00:27:39,423
the paramedics;
you can check with them.

00:27:39,490 --> 00:27:41,158
Charlotte died around 2:00 a.m.

00:27:41,225 --> 00:27:42,459
Where were you then?

00:27:42,526 --> 00:27:45,162
I was out with Marty
trying to walk off his high

00:27:45,229 --> 00:27:46,430
to keep him out of trouble.

00:27:46,497 --> 00:27:48,966
Does Crackhead Marty
have a last name?

00:27:49,033 --> 00:27:50,601
I-I don't know.

00:27:50,668 --> 00:27:52,770
You know, Father, listen,

00:27:52,837 --> 00:27:54,505
I'm telling you,
these answers--

00:27:54,572 --> 00:27:57,074
none of them work for me.

00:27:57,141 --> 00:27:59,143
Well, then put me in jail.

00:27:59,210 --> 00:28:01,612
I'll still be doing exactly
the same work I'm doing out here

00:28:01,679 --> 00:28:03,113
with exactly the same results.

00:28:03,180 --> 00:28:04,381
I don't want to do that.

00:28:04,448 --> 00:28:06,517
(knocking)

00:28:07,852 --> 00:28:08,819
BRASS:
Sister Bridget?

00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:12,489
I think you should
see this, Cap.

00:28:12,556 --> 00:28:13,958
I'm sorry I didn't

00:28:14,024 --> 00:28:15,092
come forward
sooner, Father.

00:28:15,159 --> 00:28:17,127
We caught her trying to bring
this into the building.

00:28:17,194 --> 00:28:18,929
This is the hammer I used
to build the cross.

00:28:18,996 --> 00:28:19,930
FRANK:
No, no, she didn't.

00:28:19,997 --> 00:28:22,032
She must've got that
out of my office

00:28:22,099 --> 00:28:23,033
at the shelter.

00:28:23,100 --> 00:28:24,635
I took it off Marty.

00:28:24,702 --> 00:28:26,337
Father, sit down, please.

00:28:26,403 --> 00:28:29,173
Sister, excuse me, but...

00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:31,275
could you tell us
how you managed to haul

00:28:31,342 --> 00:28:33,310
the victim's body
to the top of the scaffolding?

00:28:33,377 --> 00:28:35,513
I used the rope and the pulley,

00:28:35,579 --> 00:28:37,615
the one the
workmen use.

00:28:37,681 --> 00:28:38,549
But why did you kill her?

00:28:38,616 --> 00:28:41,118
Because she had to be stopped.

00:28:41,185 --> 00:28:42,987
She was coming for Father,

00:28:43,053 --> 00:28:45,456
and I couldn't
let that happen.

00:28:45,523 --> 00:28:47,725
Now...

00:28:47,791 --> 00:28:49,660
do your job.

00:28:49,727 --> 00:28:51,028
Arrest me.

00:28:51,095 --> 00:28:54,465
Sister, how much do you weigh?

00:28:54,532 --> 00:28:56,667
123 pounds.

00:28:56,734 --> 00:28:59,770
It's a question of physics.

00:28:59,837 --> 00:29:03,007
Charlotte weighed 140 pounds,
plus the weight of the cross.

00:29:03,073 --> 00:29:05,309
You don't weigh enough
or have enough strength

00:29:05,376 --> 00:29:08,312
to have hoisted the body
17 feet into the air.

00:29:08,379 --> 00:29:11,549
It was a miracle.

00:29:13,884 --> 00:29:17,454
The only miracle is I'm not
charging you with obstruction.

00:29:17,521 --> 00:29:19,089
♪ ♪

00:29:48,986 --> 00:29:52,022
(beeping)

00:30:06,971 --> 00:30:10,674
Father Frank.

00:30:10,741 --> 00:30:12,576
The blood on the hammer
is a match

00:30:12,643 --> 00:30:14,512
to the blood found
on the Father's clothes,

00:30:14,578 --> 00:30:17,448
but none of it is
from Charlotte.

00:30:17,515 --> 00:30:19,850
Well, you know, he told me

00:30:19,917 --> 00:30:22,086
that he broke up
a fight at the shelter.

00:30:22,152 --> 00:30:24,455
I think Sister Bridget
found the bloody hammer

00:30:24,522 --> 00:30:25,956
and confessed to the murder

00:30:26,023 --> 00:30:27,958
because she thought
Father Frank was guilty.

00:30:28,025 --> 00:30:30,561
If she thinks he did it,
maybe he did it.

00:30:30,628 --> 00:30:32,630
But why does she think

00:30:32,696 --> 00:30:34,698
that he did it?

00:30:37,034 --> 00:30:38,269
You know,

00:30:38,335 --> 00:30:40,404
his move from St. Bart's

00:30:40,471 --> 00:30:41,772
to St. Jude's involved

00:30:41,839 --> 00:30:44,108
a female parishioner
who committed suicide.

00:30:44,175 --> 00:30:46,076
No charges were filed,

00:30:46,143 --> 00:30:49,747
but the parish board
asked that he be removed.

00:30:49,813 --> 00:30:51,415
SIDLE:
I can do you one better.

00:30:51,482 --> 00:30:54,618
Catherine found two sets
of semen stains

00:30:54,685 --> 00:30:55,719
on Charlotte's bedding.

00:30:55,786 --> 00:30:57,388
Unknown contributor
on the bed skirt.

00:30:57,454 --> 00:30:59,657
Probably doesn't
get washed as often.

00:30:59,723 --> 00:31:03,093
But the one on the sheet
is a match to Father Frank.

00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:04,562
It's probably
more recent.

00:31:04,628 --> 00:31:07,531
And here is
the big thing:

00:31:07,598 --> 00:31:09,500
Uh, Doc Robbins says
that Charlotte was

00:31:09,567 --> 00:31:11,502
about ten weeks pregnant.

00:31:11,569 --> 00:31:13,370
STOKES:
Maybe he's the unwilling

00:31:13,437 --> 00:31:14,872
father of her unborn child.

00:31:14,939 --> 00:31:18,542
Well, DNA will
give us a profile.

00:31:18,609 --> 00:31:21,178
One more thing
that he did not tell us.

00:31:21,245 --> 00:31:23,547
We didn't ask.

00:31:23,614 --> 00:31:24,682
BRASS:
I don't know, I mean,

00:31:24,748 --> 00:31:25,950
most people give
their friends,

00:31:26,016 --> 00:31:29,019
uh, subscriptions to
Fruit of the Month club.

00:31:29,086 --> 00:31:30,221
(chuckling)

00:31:30,287 --> 00:31:32,890
But you gave your friend
Charlotte a condo and a car.

00:31:32,957 --> 00:31:35,392
It's like I told you before,
I was helping her out.

00:31:35,459 --> 00:31:37,461
I was letting her live there
and use the car

00:31:37,528 --> 00:31:38,696
till she got on her feet.

00:31:38,762 --> 00:31:40,598
She came back to Vegas
broke and strung out,

00:31:40,664 --> 00:31:42,132
and I was helping her.

00:31:42,199 --> 00:31:44,001
So it was supposed to
be a short-term thing?

00:31:44,068 --> 00:31:46,237
It was supposed to be
short-term, but it was endless.

00:31:46,303 --> 00:31:47,671
Sort of like
renovating St. Jude's.

00:31:47,738 --> 00:31:49,507
So is that what the fight
in the church was about?

00:31:49,573 --> 00:31:51,876
No, that's not
what the fight was about.

00:31:51,942 --> 00:31:53,978
I went to talk to him
about Charlotte.

00:31:54,044 --> 00:31:55,546
I thought maybe

00:31:55,613 --> 00:31:57,815
taking the car back had
something to do with her death.

00:31:57,882 --> 00:31:59,583
I don't know. Then he said
something; I said...

00:31:59,650 --> 00:32:01,352
I don't even remember,
to tell you the truth.

00:32:01,418 --> 00:32:02,987
But I'll tell you this:
he lost it.

00:32:03,053 --> 00:32:04,455
I've never seen
Frank like that.

00:32:04,522 --> 00:32:05,956
So do you always have
personal conversations

00:32:06,023 --> 00:32:06,991
in the confessional?

00:32:07,057 --> 00:32:08,425
Can't talk to him in his office

00:32:08,492 --> 00:32:10,427
with that Sister Bridget
hovering around.

00:32:10,494 --> 00:32:12,463
Besides, I'd never want
his relationship with Charlotte

00:32:12,530 --> 00:32:14,398
to be open to misinterpretation.

00:32:14,465 --> 00:32:15,599
Now, why would
their relationship

00:32:15,666 --> 00:32:16,867
be open to misinterpretation?

00:32:16,934 --> 00:32:19,904
They were more than friends.

00:32:21,939 --> 00:32:24,208
GRISSOM:
Going by her scrapbook,

00:32:24,275 --> 00:32:26,410
this seems to have been

00:32:26,477 --> 00:32:29,914
a golden time in Charlotte's
life-- high school.

00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:32,616
There's a lot of pictures
of the three of them together,

00:32:32,683 --> 00:32:35,853
but the only two-shots
are of Frank and Charlotte

00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:37,087
except for this one.

00:32:38,122 --> 00:32:41,759
Evidently, she went
to her prom with Cody.

00:32:41,825 --> 00:32:43,093
STOKES:
She looks thrilled. <i>(sarcastic)</i>

00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:45,863
The next picture of Frank,

00:32:45,930 --> 00:32:48,065
he's in a seminary.

00:32:48,132 --> 00:32:49,733
Maybe, uh,

00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:52,636
giving up Charlotte

00:32:52,703 --> 00:32:55,139
was the sacrifice he made
to join the Church.

00:33:07,885 --> 00:33:10,621
I need to ask you
a few more questions.

00:33:10,688 --> 00:33:14,124
Go ahead and ask the question
you really want to know.

00:33:14,191 --> 00:33:16,594
Who killed Charlotte Danville?

00:33:19,830 --> 00:33:22,199
I did.

00:33:24,835 --> 00:33:27,972
(sighs)

00:33:34,415 --> 00:33:35,516
(elevator bell dings)

00:33:35,583 --> 00:33:37,384
Single malt express
is leaving the station

00:33:37,451 --> 00:33:38,986
as soon as
I get home.

00:33:39,053 --> 00:33:42,256
Look, I know it sounds nuts,
but this is not the way

00:33:42,323 --> 00:33:44,358
a resurrection theologian would
kill his pregnant mistress.

00:33:44,425 --> 00:33:45,526
He confessed.

00:33:45,593 --> 00:33:47,394
He's a Catholic.
They're full of guilt.

00:33:47,461 --> 00:33:48,996
He's a priest,
for God's sakes.

00:33:49,063 --> 00:33:50,831
That's the whole point
of the priesthood.

00:33:50,898 --> 00:33:52,366
No sleeping around.

00:33:52,433 --> 00:33:53,867
More energy for

00:33:53,934 --> 00:33:55,869
good works and
noble deeds.

00:33:55,936 --> 00:33:57,438
Now you find me some evidence

00:33:57,504 --> 00:33:59,640
to exonerate the good Father,
and we'll talk.

00:34:09,450 --> 00:34:12,453
WILLOWS:
Hi. I heard Grissom wants us
to keep digging.

00:34:12,519 --> 00:34:14,088
This Charlotte's car?

00:34:14,154 --> 00:34:15,856
Yeah.

00:34:15,923 --> 00:34:19,126
I found blood smears,
but they've been washed.

00:34:19,193 --> 00:34:23,030
Cody said he repo'd
the car at the club

00:34:23,097 --> 00:34:24,932
and drove it back to the lot.

00:34:24,999 --> 00:34:27,268
There shouldn't be any blood
in this car.

00:34:27,334 --> 00:34:29,236
Well, unless Father Frank
drove it that night,

00:34:29,303 --> 00:34:30,971
and we've got no reason
to believe

00:34:31,038 --> 00:34:32,139
that he did.

00:34:32,206 --> 00:34:33,574
Which brings us back to Cody.

00:34:33,641 --> 00:34:35,709
Do you have a big enough sample
for DNA?

00:34:35,776 --> 00:34:37,177
No.

00:34:37,244 --> 00:34:39,813
But I do know

00:34:39,880 --> 00:34:42,583
one spot the
detailers never hit.

00:34:48,289 --> 00:34:50,157
Bloody shoe impression
on the brake pedal.

00:34:50,224 --> 00:34:51,959
Well, I'll compare it
to Father Frank's shoes.

00:34:52,026 --> 00:34:54,662
If it's not a match, I'll get
a warrant for Cody's shoes.

00:34:54,728 --> 00:34:56,764
I'll get a sample
of the blood to DNA.

00:34:58,566 --> 00:35:00,634
CODY:
I'm trying to shoot
a commercial here,

00:35:00,701 --> 00:35:02,770
so I don't see
why this can't wait.

00:35:02,836 --> 00:35:03,938
I can't even read this,

00:35:04,004 --> 00:35:06,607
so why don't you tell me
what it is that you want?

00:35:06,674 --> 00:35:08,642
Your boots and a DNA sample.

00:35:08,709 --> 00:35:09,877
Well, there's my wife.

00:35:09,944 --> 00:35:11,111
Candy!

00:35:11,178 --> 00:35:13,814
Get my damn lawyer
on the phone now.
What's wrong?

00:35:13,881 --> 00:35:16,250
Would... would you just do it,
please?

00:35:16,317 --> 00:35:17,184
We found rust-colored fur

00:35:17,251 --> 00:35:19,253
on the scaffold
at the crime scene.

00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:20,921
CURTIS:
Well, I'll call

00:35:20,988 --> 00:35:24,458
a judge and get him to amend
the warrant to include the vest.

00:35:24,525 --> 00:35:26,694
J-J-J-J-J-J... Hold on
for a minute, all right?

00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:28,128
Would you just hang on?

00:35:28,195 --> 00:35:30,464
Hey, I found these
in his office.

00:35:30,531 --> 00:35:32,666
Positive for blood
on the right sole.

00:35:32,733 --> 00:35:34,068
Where's my wife?

00:35:34,134 --> 00:35:35,603
Candy?!

00:35:35,669 --> 00:35:37,304
Well, Big Hombre,

00:35:37,371 --> 00:35:39,607
it looks like
you're going to the hoosegow.

00:35:39,673 --> 00:35:42,109
(panting)

00:35:42,176 --> 00:35:45,312
So, you don't like crucifixes,
but maybe you made an exception

00:35:45,379 --> 00:35:47,982
when you found out
Charlotte was pregnant, hmm?

00:35:48,048 --> 00:35:51,485
GRISSOM:
Father...

00:35:51,552 --> 00:35:53,320
I want you to take
a look at this.

00:36:01,962 --> 00:36:03,964
I'm responsible for her murder.

00:36:04,031 --> 00:36:06,367
I could never do that.

00:36:06,433 --> 00:36:07,635
In my world, Father,

00:36:07,701 --> 00:36:09,670
you're either guilty
or innocent.

00:36:09,737 --> 00:36:12,139
Well, in my world,
you can be both.

00:36:12,206 --> 00:36:14,308
The blood on your boot
is Charlotte's.

00:36:14,375 --> 00:36:16,710
Your footprint was found
on the brake pedal

00:36:16,777 --> 00:36:18,879
of her car
in blood.

00:36:18,946 --> 00:36:22,349
The lab also matched hair
from your fur vest

00:36:22,416 --> 00:36:24,318
to hair found dried

00:36:24,385 --> 00:36:26,854
in the blood of the
victim in the church.

00:36:26,921 --> 00:36:29,390
(laughs)

00:36:29,456 --> 00:36:33,427
Now matter how much evidence
you have, I'm the Big Hombre.

00:36:33,494 --> 00:36:37,331
I get whatever I want,
including store-bought justice.

00:36:37,398 --> 00:36:39,833
And yet, the one thing
you couldn't get

00:36:39,900 --> 00:36:42,169
was Charlotte's love.

00:36:42,236 --> 00:36:43,737
Yeah, like I said,

00:36:43,804 --> 00:36:47,541
I only saw her that last time
to get the car.

00:36:47,608 --> 00:36:51,011
♪ Come the day you're mine ♪
(men scatting along)

00:36:51,078 --> 00:36:55,382
♪ Come the day you're mine ♪

00:36:55,449 --> 00:36:58,452
♪ Come the day you're ♪

00:36:58,519 --> 00:37:03,023
♪ Mine. ♪

00:37:03,090 --> 00:37:05,759
(applause)

00:37:05,826 --> 00:37:07,394
Thanks for coming.

00:37:07,461 --> 00:37:10,064
Come on. I'd come every night
if you wanted me to.

00:37:10,130 --> 00:37:12,600
You know that.

00:37:12,666 --> 00:37:14,868
Here's the car back.

00:37:14,935 --> 00:37:17,271
You really are a good friend.

00:37:17,338 --> 00:37:20,708
No, you gave her the car.

00:37:20,774 --> 00:37:23,377
You gave her everything.

00:37:23,444 --> 00:37:26,580
And how did she pay you back?

00:37:26,647 --> 00:37:28,616
She dumped you
for your best friend.

00:37:28,682 --> 00:37:32,419
(keys jangling)
Here's the car back.

00:37:32,486 --> 00:37:33,921
And I'm moving.

00:37:33,988 --> 00:37:35,422
Why would you do that?

00:37:35,489 --> 00:37:36,824
I can't do this anymore.

00:37:36,890 --> 00:37:38,626
It's not right.

00:37:38,692 --> 00:37:40,895
I'm in love with another man.

00:37:40,961 --> 00:37:42,663
I'm sorry, Cody.

00:37:42,730 --> 00:37:44,331
That's what you got for me?

00:37:44,398 --> 00:37:45,933
You got, you're sorry?

00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:47,534
I'm sorry, too.

00:37:48,535 --> 00:37:50,771
GRISSOM:
We, uh,

00:37:50,838 --> 00:37:52,873
found a letter
you wrote to the Bishop

00:37:52,940 --> 00:37:54,441
and pulled it
off your computer.

00:37:54,508 --> 00:37:58,312
"The spirit has left
my vocation.

00:37:58,379 --> 00:38:00,381
"I've crossed a line
in my discipline

00:38:00,447 --> 00:38:02,850
"and committed an act
that has left me unfit

00:38:02,917 --> 00:38:04,685
for the priesthood."

00:38:06,954 --> 00:38:08,923
What act is that?

00:38:08,989 --> 00:38:12,593
Putting my love for Charlotte
above my love for God.

00:38:12,660 --> 00:38:14,428
So, you were leaving
the priesthood?

00:38:14,495 --> 00:38:16,530
I was leaving
because I loved her,

00:38:16,597 --> 00:38:20,067
and I wanted to be with her
in all ways.

00:38:20,134 --> 00:38:22,136
Her dying doesn't change that.

00:38:22,202 --> 00:38:23,337
I still love her.

00:38:23,404 --> 00:38:25,239
I talked to the Monsignor.

00:38:25,306 --> 00:38:27,975
It's a complicated process,
but I told him I'm leaving.

00:38:28,042 --> 00:38:29,276
Are you sure?

00:38:29,343 --> 00:38:31,178
I prayed about it.

00:38:31,245 --> 00:38:33,647
What came to me was
that God is love.

00:38:33,714 --> 00:38:36,183
Wherever there is true love,
God is, as well.

00:38:36,250 --> 00:38:39,053
I have to follow my heart.

00:38:39,119 --> 00:38:41,388
And we only made love once,

00:38:41,455 --> 00:38:43,424
but in the wake of that,

00:38:43,490 --> 00:38:46,627
I found the husband in me,

00:38:46,694 --> 00:38:48,662
the father in me.

00:38:48,729 --> 00:38:51,632
I wanted
to be those men for her.

00:38:51,699 --> 00:38:54,435
And I always loved her.

00:38:56,270 --> 00:38:57,538
And what if the baby
wasn't yours?

00:38:57,605 --> 00:38:59,707
A child is always welcome.

00:38:59,773 --> 00:39:02,843
Yeah, I decorated her condo,
you know that?

00:39:02,910 --> 00:39:05,145
I bought her that car.

00:39:05,212 --> 00:39:08,182
Special-ordered the paint
to match the color of her eyes.

00:39:08,249 --> 00:39:11,485
She didn't care as long
as she had a place to stay.

00:39:11,552 --> 00:39:12,886
That's all she cared about.

00:39:12,953 --> 00:39:15,889
She cared about Father Frank,
didn't she?

00:39:15,956 --> 00:39:18,926
Did you suspect that she
was leaving you for him?

00:39:18,993 --> 00:39:21,629
Should have, but I didn't.

00:39:24,431 --> 00:39:25,933
What are you doing here?

00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:28,669
Look, I'm sorry about
the dress, all right?

00:39:28,736 --> 00:39:30,571
I have to get back to the club.

00:39:30,638 --> 00:39:31,906
Wait, wait, wait.

00:39:31,972 --> 00:39:34,241
I want to know who
you're leaving me for.

00:39:34,308 --> 00:39:35,943
No.
(slaps)

00:39:36,010 --> 00:39:37,011
(groaning)

00:39:37,077 --> 00:39:38,445
What is that?

00:39:41,181 --> 00:39:42,349
It's Frank, isn't it?

00:39:42,416 --> 00:39:43,517
(shouting):
<i>Isn't it?</i>

00:39:43,584 --> 00:39:47,087
(groaning)
It's always
been Frank.

00:39:48,422 --> 00:39:50,291
(choking)

00:39:50,357 --> 00:39:51,725
You know, he doesn't think

00:39:51,792 --> 00:39:52,927
you did it.

00:39:52,993 --> 00:39:54,862
But I think

00:39:54,929 --> 00:39:56,730
that you know
who killed Charlotte.

00:39:56,797 --> 00:40:00,768
He came to the church that day
to confess, didn't he?

00:40:00,834 --> 00:40:05,105
Bless me, Father,
for I have sinned.

00:40:05,172 --> 00:40:07,541
My last confession
was two weeks ago.

00:40:07,608 --> 00:40:09,777
I lied to my wife seven times.

00:40:09,843 --> 00:40:13,247
I cheated an old lady
out of a classic car.

00:40:13,314 --> 00:40:16,283
And I killed my best friend
for cheating on me with you.

00:40:17,718 --> 00:40:19,620
You know I can't discuss that.

00:40:21,855 --> 00:40:25,292
You know, in Vegas,
it's routine

00:40:25,359 --> 00:40:28,629
to hear the most heinous sins,
and as a priest, you listen,

00:40:28,696 --> 00:40:30,965
and in Christ's name,
you forgive.

00:40:31,031 --> 00:40:33,367
I knew she'd go running to him.

00:40:33,434 --> 00:40:37,304
She'd always run back to Frank,
and I knew he wouldn't be there.

00:40:37,371 --> 00:40:39,540
He was never there.

00:40:44,912 --> 00:40:47,214
Is that when
you thought of
crucifying her

00:40:47,281 --> 00:40:49,316
in Frank's church?

00:40:54,488 --> 00:40:56,957
I don't know
how I came up with that.

00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:01,896
You know, Frank always
used to talk

00:41:01,962 --> 00:41:03,898
about the problem of human evil.

00:41:03,964 --> 00:41:05,933
How...

00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:08,869
you better watch out
'cause it'd come into you

00:41:08,936 --> 00:41:10,938
in times of despair.

00:41:15,175 --> 00:41:18,746
Something terrible
came into me that night.

00:41:48,909 --> 00:41:52,179
I loved Charlotte more
than anything.

00:41:52,246 --> 00:41:56,016
The paternity test came back.

00:41:56,083 --> 00:41:58,085
You were
the father.

00:42:00,387 --> 00:42:02,523
You killed your own baby.

00:42:06,527 --> 00:42:10,231
(sobbing)

00:42:34,688 --> 00:42:36,991
You were my friend.

00:42:38,926 --> 00:42:40,661
You should have come
to me like a man.

00:42:48,702 --> 00:42:51,572
Can you forgive him?

00:42:51,639 --> 00:42:53,841
That's Christ's mandate.

00:42:53,908 --> 00:42:55,876
You know what that means.

00:42:55,943 --> 00:42:57,878
You have no choice.

